#standard gitignore file for a ROS2 package, it ignores the build, install and log folders generated by colcon,
#as well as various build and editor artifacts that are not relevant to the project.
#It also ignores the __pycache__ and .cache folders generated by Python, which are not relevant to the project and can be safely ignored. 
#The .vscode folder is ignored, but the extensions.json and settings.json files are not ignored, as they contain important information about the extensions and settings used in the project.
# The .idea folder is ignored, as it is generated by the IntelliJ IDE and is not relevant to the project. The .DS_Store file is ignored, as it is generated by macOS and is not relevant to the project.

# colcon/CMake output
build/
install/
log/

# various build/editor artifacts
*.pyc
*.iml
*.swp
.project
.pydevproject
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/
!.vscode/extensions.json
!.vscode/settings.json
__pycache__/
.cache/
